# Secrets and Logging Safety

Apply whenever touching auth, env configuration, logging, or commits.

## Never do

- Commit real secrets (`.env`, tokens, private keys, credentials files).
- Log raw authorization headers, JWT values, passwords, or full auth payloads.
- Echo secrets in docs, examples, or test snapshots.

## Required behavior

- Use placeholders in docs/examples (`<TOKEN_SECRET>`, `<DATABASE_URL>`).
- Keep secrets in runtime environment configuration only.
- If secret-like files are about to be staged, stop and ask for explicit user confirmation.

## Commit-time guardrails

- Prefer excluding secret-like files by default.
- If user explicitly approves inclusion, confirm exact file names before staging.
